author: Kevin
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2019
review_content: So I’m out of work for 3-4 months from shoulder surgery,  so I decided to do a little testing. I was sick of buying 2032 battery’s and being not sure if I bought junk or something good. I had bought some cheaper ones and they had all since expired so it was time to buy more. I figured I would do the usual and read some reviews, weigh in the 4+5 stars to see what present they took up, weigh in the price, and read reviews. So I found what I felt were the top 3 rated and purchased them.Because my son and I are avid remote control car races I have a fairly high end charger that I can trick into discharging these small batteries. Even on the lowest setting it discharges a little high. The low setting was .1 amp discharge. But I used it all the same and looked to see how long they would discharge before the reached a cut off voltage of 1.8v. Plus I recorded starting volts of each battery and end rebounded volts after disconnecting them in a same timely fashion for each. GloFX seem to be the champion by far. Note I only tested 1 of each. It’s on my dime so I only tested 1. See the pictures with the results to make your own conclusions. Have a great day
title: So I tested 3 different brands... see my results

author: batray
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2019
review_content: These batteries are counterfeit crap.  They measure fine open circuit, but the voltage drops quickly under even a light (<100uA) load.  Notice the difference in fonts of the genuine Energizer and this piece of counterfeit crap.  Do not buy these are anything from this vendor!!
title: counterfeit crap!!

author: Dubs

I'm getting LESS THAN ONE MONTH!Based on the reviews, there's clearly something wrong with many of the batteries they send if you purchase them from this listing.

date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2018
review_content: Second Purchase  10/2019Energizer Batteries CR2032BP-6Pros:–Price and quantity–Batteries and package as shown in ad, made in Indonesia, expiration 03/2029Cons:–NoneFirst Purchase  03/2018Pros:--Price, quantity, fresh product--Happily, expiration date shows 03/2025--was afraid seller would be pushing products close to expiration--see pic attached.Item on left is current purchase, expiration 03/2025; item on right purchased 10/2015 with an expiration date of 03/2023Use a lot of this model in PCs, calculator, car FOB, wireless door sensors.  Will buy from this seller again.Stamped "Made In Indonesia", no mention of Mercury Free so don't know.

author: barry
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2019
review_content: I need the 2032 batteries in so many things and Energizer is my favorite brand of batteries.  Best with longevity and performance for sure. author: V. Armstrong
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2019
review_content: I got 4 of 2032, I used my Pulse Load 3V Lithium battery tester to test the new 2032 and got a failed result, I trying a nother new 2032 and also got the failed result, than I tried to find an expiration date on back of the 2032 box but only found the copy right date of 2017, if it was made 2017 and now is April 2019 no wander it failed the test...

author: Luvnmac
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2019
review_content: Amazon is awesome for making sure customers are satisfied. Being a Prime member allows efficient returns and refunds.  These batteries were dead upon arrival.  Wondered why they died so quickly.  Purchased a battery tester and all of them tested on the higher end of dead/replace.  These batteries are used for sensors with security system. I do not suggest buying these as it appears many small cell batteries will often arrive dead.  Always test your batteries upon arrival to avoid missing your window of time for return/refund.  Disappointed but very happy Amazon made it right.  Thank you, Amazon! :)

author: Nice shopper
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2019

author: Vidiot
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2018
review_content: I used to get my CR2032 cells from the BJs Wholesale club when Duracell has coupons. After switching to these Energizers, the scale has been lasting noticeably longer.  It's not an issue of expiration dates since the Duracells I used to get always had a date far out in the future.

author: Rodger Kingston
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2019
review_content: I bought these batteries for my Omron pedometer. The previous battery lasted for several years of regular use. The first one of these Energizer batteries has died in less than three months. I would like a refund.

author: Ray C FL
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2017
review_content: I would give this five stars, except that the first battery I tried quit after about a day. This was for the remote for a 2014 Honda Odyssey. I had gotten a low battery warning, and had ordered these replacements. The first battery lasted a couple of days, then I got the warning again with the new battery. I tried using the second Honda fob with its original battery, and that worked OK, so the problem had to be in the replacement battery. I removed it, installed a second battery from the same pack, and that one has been working fine for a couple of weeks. I haven't tried the other two batteries. With just one failure, I have no statistics to tell me this happens half the time or once in a thousand. There's no evidence that the batteries are counterfeit, they look exactly like the battery I replaced. If this battery lasts two years like the originals, I won't know for a long time whether the other two are good or not. Replacing a battery in the Honda fob involves disassembling it into several pieces, which I don't want to do for at least another two years. I expect this one to last two years also.
title: 25% Failure Rate?

author: Tom
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2018
review_content: I wouldn't waste your money.  I bought these for my activity tracker, thinking I could save some money after spending $10 at the battery store for two of them. Even though only $3, complete waste of money.

author: BEJ
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2019
review_content: I use these for the key fob on my Lojack system for my SUV. author: pendles621
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2017
review_content: I wasn't paying attention so I thought these were DURACELL batteries. They are NOT. The word energizer and the tricky packaging is designed to fool the customer. I was NOT paying attention. I have cancelled the subscription to this product and I am now hunting for Duracell. I have found a 4 pack for 8.29 on Amazon. Since those truly ARE Duracell I am happy to pay an additional 3 dollars. I will cross my fingers that they will be good quality.
title: BEWARE of tricky packaging. Don't buy these.

author: Nicole
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2020
review_content: When I purchased these batteries I thought, that's a great deal, a six pack of these Energizer CR2032 Batteries for under $6.00, less than $1.00 per battery.  Great Price, from Energizer, great brand RIGHT!Under normal use these batteries should last 2-5 years.  It states in the add it will hold power for 10 years.NOT THIS PACK.  I did not even get 10 months. This was delivered in February.  I have already had to throw three out as they died within 6 weeks of use.  Today I put the 4th one into a calculator, and immediately upon turning it on, the device told me that the battery was LOW.I thought it was me, I was suspicious.  I did not want to write a bad review, but I now realize that these batteries must be old, or something was wrong with them.The price is right, but you will likely have to replace them much sooner than you expect.

author: Kate B.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2019
review_content: I needed these batteries for Christmas decorations and ordered these due to the brand and also the fact it was a good value! The batteries come in a package that is back with a reinforced plastic/foil. Each battery is separate from the other so you have to open each one individually. It was difficult for me to open and required me using a knife. While a little inconvenient, as a family with 3 young kids in it and 1 of those who puts everything in their mouth, I wholly appreciate the fact it would be unbelievably hard for them to get into the package. And the fact each battery is kept separate, even if they got in one, they couldn't get to any other battery without somehow getting the next spot open.Each battery also comes with a protective sticker to peel on the side you need to put down.Worked amazing for Christmas ornaments and would recommend
title: Child safe package and good value for a good brand!

author: DBF
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2019
review_content: Normal 2032 batteries last about one year in my bicycle computer. These are lasting two weeks. Expiration date one package lists 2025.

author: Gorlank

author: Christopher Boudreaux
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2020
review_content: Title says it all....such a great deal compared to stores. There's a drug store very near me that I buy lots of different things from. The name rhymes with FallPreens.Now at this drug store the price for this exact same package of batteries is, as of yesterday, $18.99! They want $19 for 6 batteries, or $7 for just one, and I got all 6 for just over $5. How this store can get away with such overpriced items is beyond me. Maybe they're circling the drain of bankruptcy and overriding everything in some desperate attempt to stay afloat I don't know. But what I do know is that id NEVER buy batteries from them. Another big box retailer that rhymes with FallWart is also insanely overpriced. They buy for far less than what I paid here on Amazon yet want 1000% markup profit plus some. From here on out, whenever possible, I'll be buying everything I can online and staying far away from the cultures that call themselves retailers. They are robbing us blind and this is but one example. I love these batteties and this size typically works in everything i need a cell of this type in. The numbers CR2032 correspond to the actual size of the cell itself. They're 20mm wide and 3.2mm thick hence 2032. Almost all batteries follow this same rule. The big 18650 batteries are 18mm wide and 65mm long as an example. These are such a good price I bought 2 packs!
title: Such a great price compared to brick and mortar stores

author: MHermawan
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2020
review_content: Terrible batteries. No matter how low the price, if the batteries don’t work, they’re overpriced!Originally, 4 out of the 6 batteries  didn’t work. The seller was very good and sent me a replacement right away.  Unfortunately, within 5 days, the 2 batteries that were working are already dead!!!!I think maybe they have a bunch of old batteries that didn’t sell in the warehouse, and ship them out since supposedly, the batteries have a shelf life of 10 years....but the 10 years may have already passed in the warehouse and close to end of life when shipped to buyer!

author: Katrina
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2018
review_content: Gave these a try twice because they aren't too expensive, but both times the batteries barely had a charge.I use them in my blood glucose meter and one battery was so bad I checked my sugars once and the meter complained the battery was dead already. To put that in perspective, I check with this meter once a day, when it has good batteries I might replace them twice a year... if that. Needlessly to say I won't be buying these again :/

author: J. Ashar
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2019
review_content: I currently own two Nissan vehicles including a 2015 Rogue and a 2016 Murano.  Recently, whenever I turned on both vehicles, a warning message popped up saying that the batteries for the keys were getting weaker and needed replacing.  I didn't want to go all the way to the dealership to get this taken care of, so I looked up a video on YouTube.  On YouTube, I found others in the same situation as me, and they were able to showcase the steps needed to open the key fob and which battery to buy to replace the old one.  I found that I needed a 3 volt battery (CR2032).Searching through Amazon, I found many different options.  However, the listing for   Energizer           which included 6 batteries for $4.99 caught my attention.  It had an orange "#1 Best Seller" badge at the top of the Amazon page, so I hoped it would be a trustworthy product.  When the batteries arrived, I quickly disassembled my Nissan key fobs and replaced both batteries.  They both worked right away, and I had zero issues with the batteries through 1-week of use.  I will report back if these batteries fail, but as of right now, they deserve a 5/5 rating.
title: Great battery replacements for Nissan key fobs!

author: Who me?
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2019
review_content: I use a product called tile to help find my Car & House key.  I needed to replace the batteries in both tiles, The House key went without a hitch when I tried using the tile to retrieve my car key It would not play a musical tone to tell me where it is. On my phone app, it told me tied to replace your battery.For anybody who's thinking, I mixed up batteries and put the old one in... no, energizer Is engraved on the top new battery, the old battery has Tile in graved on the top.

author: electronicguru77

review_content: Ordered from a 3rd party seller and fulfilled by Amazon. Used it to replace battery in a tile. Within a week the Tile app said that the battery had to be replaced. author: William M. Gibson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 16, 2019
review_content: I have a number of devices that use this type of battery.  They're easy to find at the grocery store or hardware store, but they're not cheap.  Price on Amazon represents great value.Not sure what you can say about a battery.  If you're familiar with this style of battery, you know what it looks like and you know what it does.  I had no problem with any DOA batteries in this pack, and no problem with performance or how long they last.  They just do what what they're supposed to do and last as long as they're supposed to, which is what you want out of a battery.

author: AR
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2020
review_content: Bought these a few months ago. They have an expiry date of March 2029. I put them in my car remote key and it worked well for the first few days, then after that, I have to put the keys right up against the door handle and try it a few times before it will work. This week I had to replace batteries in my bathroom scale and the other 2 batteries still in the package did not work. I tested them and they were dead.I emailed Energizer and they are investigating. Not sure if it makes a difference but the package has a date of 2018 (though I just bought them this year) and these were made in Indonesia.

author: Angela W
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2017
review_content: Batteries were nearly dead on arrival.  Would barely light the LED on the remote. author: C Kadien
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2019
review_content: The package had a use by date of 02-2026 but when I put them in my remote it showed they were DEAD. Sadly the ones I were replacing had more life than the new ones. cf-course the return window closed days before I tried them..

author: decadeindc
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2020
review_content: These coin batteries seem to have a decent charge and none have run out of juice yet at the three-week mark. No duds either. I haven't busted out the voltmeter, but they've been powering various devices consistently well for more than two weeks now (I've used eight or so - ordered two packs). Only time will tell if they're fully charged, but none of the horror stories of other brands where every third battery lasts 1-2 days.These batteries came packaged differently than what's shown in the product listing. It came as a small box that held six individually packaged batteries instead of a pack of six together. That didn't matter at all to me. Maybe it matters to someone.Lastly, just wish these had faster shipping times, but there are limits on who will ship batteries and by what method. They're hard to find locally, so I keep a note with the batteries to reorder with three remaining so there's enough time to ship.

author: MG
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2020
review_content: Finally got around to actually using one of these after having them stored in a dry, cool closet for about half a year.  Packaging looks really shady and nothing at all like the photographs on the item page, but who knows?  maybe they're legit Energizer batteries that were some sort of non-retail OEM intended to be shipped to corporations to put inside the garage door openers when they're new?That being said, not only did the first one work without issue, but I had more distance with my off-brand opener than I even knew it was capable of after putting this new battery in there.  They just had an off-brand battery with it that lasted for years but I always had to be right up to the door to use it.  Now with this Energizer(?) battery inside it I can open the garage door from inside my house with the same clicker.I don't know if I'll ever even get around to using the other 5 batteries before they go bad, but that's why I bought a 6 pack for this low price just hoping that at least one of them worked.  Would buy again.
title: Not sure if they're legit, but they work really good

author: TechieShopper
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2020
review_content: I've tried replacing my pedometer with two batteries from this package and neither of them work.  The battery that I am replacing would give me a red light indicating a need for a new battery.  It had some life left in it - so I know that the issue is not with my device.  The batteries are the same type that I have ordered from Amazon and that have worked in the past.The return window is closed - and unfortunately there is nothing I can do about it.  I'm a bit disappointed that the product does not work and I've lost the money used to purchase them.

author: AddisonJ
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2018
review_content: I ordered this 4 pack thinking it was the normal 2032 from Energizer.  I was just going to have them on hand for general use.  I did not notice that the second image in the ad showed a picture of the Lithium type.  The Lithium type is what arrived.  I had also ordered a (2) pack of the lithium type for a device that I wanted a better battery for.  This 4 pack is a much better value than the 2 pack.  Wish I had know these were actually the Lithium type and I would have just ordered them and saved $4 on the 2 pack.
title: Add is a bit confusing as to the type of 2032

author: Kurt A. Pochert
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2020
review_content: The CR2032 Energizer batteries I received prove to be a genuine product, according to my testing. As noted in the picture I received six individual one cell packages, made in Japan, and received from a vendor Batteries4all in Jamaica NY. I use these batteries in various devices including my Acccu-Chek Guide glucose meter, which will not work with any counterfeit product. The counterfeit batteries fail by not delivering any kind of current to the device, even though the voltage measurement may be correct of 3+ volts or better. Even the best CR2032 are not designed to draw high currents. With a 100 ohm load for about 2 seconds the voltage should not drop below 2.5 volts for a very good cell. These cells easily pass the test. Very happy with this purchase, great value!
title: Genuine product

author: eshopaholic
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2020
review_content: No place to post anything about packaging any longer, but had to share.  An envelope would have sufficed for shipping.  What a waste.As for the product, it’s absolutely fine

author: Miss Alice
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2019
review_content: We use these batteries in step counters.  In the past, they have lasted between 4 and 6 weeks.  Suddenly, with these new pack of batteries, they are only lasting a week or 10 days.  We have two step counters and are having the same issues with both of them.

author: Adam
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2017

author: kirkcarter
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2020
review_content: Not sure if Amazon is selling knock-offs or what, but these are crap. My red dot sight has a 50k hour lifespan with one battery. It didn’t even make it a week with these.  I’m disappointed in Amazon for posting these. It shouldn’t me our job to do Amazon’s quality control.

author: Jeff Nowling
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2020

author: Frank Dutton
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2020
review_content: EXTREMELY POOR BATTERY LIFE.  I use these in a garage door opener.  Given the times we are in, I don't go out a lot - probably 3 times a week. author: R34P3RX13
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2020
review_content: My 2015 Dodge Durango R/T has a keyless pushstart and the remotes had old batteries in them. author: Sean McGrail
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2019
review_content: I bought these batteries earlier this year.  I thought that I had scored a Slickdeal.  The price was great.  What I got instead was ripped off.  The batteries were terrible. Luckily I had one of these junk batteries in my key fob and my car did not start.  I don't have a back up camera in my car so I would never have known that a child was behind my car when I went to back up.  Thank god I was ripped off with these batteries or a life would have been lost.  I have to wonder if they are even genuine Energizer batteries.  The packaging looked legit but the batteries were terrible.  Theses batteries saved a life but I do not recommend them.
